	<entry>
		<id>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FeedItem/featured/20161210000000/en</id>
		<title>December 10 Wikipedia featured article</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FeedItem/featured/20161210000000/en"/>
				<updated>2016-12-10T00:00:00Z</updated>
		
		<summary type="html">&lt;div id=&quot;mp-tfa-img&quot; style=&quot;float: left; margin: 0.5em 0.9em 0.4em 0em;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/File:Fantastic_Adventures_1940_Oct_cover.jpg&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; title=&quot;Fantastic Adventures, October 1940&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Fantastic Adventures, October 1940&quot; src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Fantastic_Adventures_1940_Oct_cover.jpg/100px-Fantastic_Adventures_1940_Oct_cover.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100&quot; height=&quot;143&quot; srcset=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Fantastic_Adventures_1940_Oct_cover.jpg/150px-Fantastic_Adventures_1940_Oct_cover.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Fantastic_Adventures_1940_Oct_cover.jpg/200px-Fantastic_Adventures_1940_Oct_cover.jpg 2x&quot; data-file-width=&quot;390&quot; data-file-height=&quot;559&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Fantastic_Adventures&quot; title=&quot;Fantastic Adventures&quot;&gt;Fantastic Adventures&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt; was an American &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Pulp_magazine&quot; title=&quot;Pulp magazine&quot;&gt;pulp&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Fantasy&quot; title=&quot;Fantasy&quot;&gt;fantasy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Science_fiction_magazine&quot; title=&quot;Science fiction magazine&quot;&gt;science fiction magazine&lt;/a&gt;, edited by &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Raymond_A._Palmer&quot; title=&quot;Raymond A. Palmer&quot;&gt;Ray Palmer&lt;/a&gt; and published from 1939 to 1953 by &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Ziff_Davis&quot; title=&quot;Ziff Davis&quot;&gt;Ziff-Davis&lt;/a&gt;. It was almost cancelled at the end of 1940, but the October 1940 issue had unexpectedly good sales, helped by a strong cover &lt;i&gt;(pictured)&lt;/i&gt; by &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/J._Allen_St._John&quot; title=&quot;J. Allen St. John&quot;&gt;J. Allen St. John&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Robert_Moore_Williams&quot; title=&quot;Robert Moore Williams&quot;&gt;Robert Moore Williams&lt;/a&gt;' &lt;i&gt;Jongor of Lost Land&lt;/i&gt;.  &lt;i&gt;Fantastic Adventures&lt;/i&gt; soon developed a reputation for light-hearted and whimsical stories.  The cover art usually focused on melodramatic action scenes; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Harold_W._McCauley&quot; title=&quot;Harold W. McCauley&quot;&gt;H.W. McCauley&lt;/a&gt;'s covers, featuring glamorous, alluring women, were among the most popular. In 1949 Palmer was replaced by &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Howard_Browne&quot; title=&quot;Howard Browne&quot;&gt;Howard Browne&lt;/a&gt;, who was knowledgeable and enthusiastic about fantasy fiction.  Browne briefly managed to improve the quality of the fiction in &lt;i&gt;Fantastic Adventures&lt;/i&gt;, and the period around 1951 has been described as the magazine's heyday.  Browne lost interest when his plan to take &lt;i&gt;Amazing Stories&lt;/i&gt; more upmarket collapsed, however, and the magazine fell back into predictability.  In 1952, Ziff-Davis launched another fantasy magazine, titled &lt;i&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Fantastic_(magazine)&quot; title=&quot;Fantastic (magazine)&quot;&gt;Fantastic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;, in a digest format; it was successful, and in March 1953 they ended &lt;i&gt;Fantastic Adventures&lt;/i&gt; in favor of &lt;i&gt;Fantastic&lt;/i&gt;. (&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Fantastic_Adventures&quot; title=&quot;Fantastic Adventures&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Full&amp;#160;article...&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;tfa-recent&quot; style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
Recently featured: &lt;div class=&quot;hlist inline&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; &lt;i&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Exsudoporus_frostii&quot; title=&quot;Exsudoporus frostii&quot;&gt;Exsudoporus frostii&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Ernie_Toshack&quot; title=&quot;Ernie Toshack&quot;&gt;Ernie Toshack&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Pennsylvania-class_battleship&quot; title=&quot;Pennsylvania-class battleship&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;Pennsylvania&lt;/i&gt;-class battleship&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
